messages.content: 9-1-1, what's your emergency?
Please help me. I'm Amanda Berry.
Do you need police, fire, or an ambulance?
I need police.
Okay. And what's going on there?
I've been kidnapped and I've been missing for 10 years and I'm here. I'm free now.
Okay. And what's your address?
22-07 Seymour Avenue.
22-07 Seymour. It looks like you're calling me from 2210?
I'm across the street, I'm using the phone.
Okay, stay there with those neighbors. Talk to the police when they get there.
Okay.
We're sending them as soon as we get a car open.
No, I need them now before he gets back.
All right. We're sending them, okay?
Okay, his name is Ariel Castro.
All right, how old is he?
He is like 52.
And you said, what was his name again?
Ariel Castro.
Is he white, black, or Hispanic? What's he wearing?
I don't know because he's not here right now.
When he left, what was he wearing?
The police are on the way, talk to them when they get there, okay?
I told you they're on the way. Talk to them when they get there, okay?
All right, okay. Thank you. Bye.
Bye.
